{"id": 7881, "title": "Ticket #7881: Add MIN_FLOCK_LEVEL knob", "description": "<blockquote>\nAdd a config knob that allows the admin to specify a set of pools that the schedd should always flock to.\n\n<p>Knob MIN_FLOCK_LEVEL sets a minimum value for each submitter's <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=FlockLevel\" title=\"Flock Level\">FlockLevel</a></span> (how many pools in the FLOCK_TO list should receive a submitter ad). The default is 0.\n\n</p><p>This can be used as a workaround for situations where the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=FlockLevel\" title=\"Flock Level\">FlockLevel</a></span> is lowered inappropriately (<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"new\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7858\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7858'); return false;\" title=\"Global Job Priority breaks flocking\">#7858</a></span>).</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2020-Nov-09 15:05:07 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\nThis issue was moved to JIRA [HTCONDOR-62].</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Nov-10 13:46</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/29ffbdb9d16cc642bc84f5b2ce5a1a29a61ce4a9\">[61633]</a></span>: Docs for config knob MIN_FLOCK_LEVEL. HTCONDOR-62 <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/tickets?ticket=7881\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7881'); return false;\" title=\"Add MIN_FLOCK_LEVEL knob\">#7881</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2020-Oct-08 13:56</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td 